Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "derek" in different forms and positions, with translations in English:

1. *Derek* je bio prazan kada sam ga pogledao. (*Derek* was empty when I looked at it.) 
2. Moram da kupim novi *derek* za svoj mobilni telefon. (I need to buy a new *derek* for my mobile phone.)
3. *Dereke* u ovoj prodavnici su skupi. (The *dereks* in this store are expensive.)
4. Stavio sam šolju na *derek*. (I put the cup on the *derek*.)
5. Ovaj *derek* je napravljen od kvalitetnog drveta. (This *derek* is made of high-quality wood.)
6. Gospodin Petrović je bio vrlo ljut kada je video da su mu *dereci* nestali. (Mr. Petrović was very angry when he saw that his *dereks* were missing.)
7. Na *dereku* je bilo ispisano ime mog prijatelja. (My friend's name was written on the *derek*.)
8. Ukoliko ne možete da nađete svoj *derek*, možete da uzmete jedan od rezervnih. (If you can't find your *derek*, you can take one of the spares.)

I hope this helps!